The paper discusses a framework for optimizing accuracy and fairness in machine learning models through selective data collection. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of crowdsourcing for data collection also suggests a potential fit for the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper addresses issues of bias and fairness, which could be relevant to the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of convex optimization, which could potentially fit under the category of control and optimization (cs.CY).
